node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 23, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'you can't choose 20 yourself and continue to stay in toxic situation.'.

node.text:
You can’t choose that toxic situation ship and also choose yourself. A choice is one or the other and one of the hardest parts about choosing yourself is that it will mean you have to make the choice between yourself and someone else, and sometimes it cannot be both. 

You can’t choose to honor yourself and your own healing and growth while continuously engaging with someone who promotes self abandonment and disrespect of your own values. Unfortunately it doesn’t work that way. You can’t do both because doing both really means ultimately choosing something over yourself. This is the hard part, this is the sacrifice. Letting some people go and no longer choosing them is the consequence. This is why it’s hard, this is why most don’t do it because it means the end of some relationships. Sometimes choosing yourself is one of the hardest things you can do for this reason, but once you do it you will understand your own strength.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 19, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, brick wall and text that says 'You're not going to feel emotionally someone validatedby who is unavailable. emotionally'.

node.text:
Continuously trying to be seen and heard by someone who has shown you that they lack the emotional intelligence to do so is not going to eventually work. If someone is showing you they aren’t able to emotionally show up and have a mature conversation or take the time and effort to try to understand you are unfortunately wasting your time and dignity. 

Sometimes we want someone to see us so badly that we deny their ability to do so. If someone is continuously being avoidant, not responding, dismissing or deterring the conversation— they’re not able to meet you where you are. They’re not ready for vulnerability and re-attempting this in different ways will not make them ready. Knowing when to let go and walk away for your own peace of mind is a love language. Stop fighting for someone who is unable to see you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BE B MORE ATTRACTED το SOMEONE THA THAT's GOOD FOR YOU'.

node.text:
Changing who and what you’re attracted to is one of the hardest things to do. It’s also the key to better more meaningful relationships. Not everything that’s familiar is necessarily healthy. 

Someone can feel like home but home may not have been a place where you were allowed to be yourself and experience meaningful connection. This is where you have to begin to question whether what you know and who you choose is something that’s helping you or hurting you. Your patterns and behaviors that you’re used to don’t always serve you. Paying attention to what and who you are attracted to will let you become more aware of things you may be tolerating in order to stay connected or close to someone. Attraction doesn’t mean compatibility or that someone is good for you. You have to separate the two and begin to train yourself to like people who treat you the way you want and deserve to be treated.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 16, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'THE WRONG PERSON: WILL HAVE YOU FEELING LIKE THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG WITH YOU.'.

node.text:
There’s nothing wrong with you, you’re just asking the wrong person to love you in a way that they may not even be capable of. Or you’re ignoring the fact that the best relationships involve compatibility. Two love languages that align and complement each other. 

Where there is friction there is misalignment. Fighting that truth will only lead to disappointment and time spent trying to be compatible with someone who just isn’t your match. Being able to let go and see where you don’t align with certain people will save you a lot of time and heartache. There’s nothing wrong with you, you’re just being asked to find someone who aligns and is able to love you the way you need it. Reassure yourself that there is strength in letting go of what’s not meant for you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 15, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'READY 0'.

node.text:
Not all relationships are meant to last. You will outgrow certain people at a time when you least want to. The point of growth is not so that it happens when you’re ready— the point of growth is so that it happens to allow you to be able to adapt to change. 

Nothing is permanent. Everything is temporary. You don’t have to be detached from everything in order to avoid ever being hurt. Being detached is unrealistic and at times unavoidable. As humans we naturally attach to things and people we love but fail to keep in mind that what you attach yourself to and define yourself by will always change. Change is the only constant and sometimes when it’s time to outgrow things we don’t want to out of fear, is sometimes the only time we’re meant to be faced with that challenge. Let things change as uncomfortable as it is— your higher self is challenging your for a reason.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 13, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text.

node.text:
Letting go is not a linear process. Sometimes, it’ll feel like you’re taking 10 steps back. Or that the progress you’ve made gets sabotaged by one specific thought or memory. Stop being so hard on yourself. 

You’re going to think about them, many times. You’re going to romanticize and have make believe conversations with yourself. You’re going to wish the outcome was different. You’re gonna want to reach out, you’re going to downplay the bad and emphasize the good. But the most important part of this whole process is that you stop expecting yourself not to feel. Understand that with time those thoughts, memories and urges become less common. The more you can trust that choosing yourself was the right thing to do, the more you will allow yourself to be human and will see these various attempts as an invitation to heal the unhealed parts of you that once allowed and accepted less.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 11, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Start having a low tolerance for mistreatment and see which relationships last. Tolerating and enabling are not an characteristics that you want to become good at. It could mean that you’re either too scared to say what you feel or you don’t believe you can actually find people of quality so you settle for the minimum and become skilled at navigating it. 

Don’t forget that relationships are voluntary. You’re in control of what you allow. You’re in control of what you tolerate or refuse to tolerate. Start speaking up and allowing yourself to attract people of quality effort and reciprocated energy.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 09, 2021.

node.text:
The best relationships help you become more of yourself, not less. Losing yourself to keep something or maintain connection is not connection, it’s self abandonment. 

Doubting and second guessing yourself are signs that there’s lack of self trust. Connection is meant to add value not to add stress and insecurity. When you start listening to yourself and paying attention to how you actually feel with certain people not just how you feel about them you start honoring your own needs. That will lead to changes and you allowing yourself to grow out of people is a sign of maturity. It’s not always a loss.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YOU ARE NOT WRONG FOR WANTING TO BE TREATED RIGHT.'.

node.text:
You’re not wrong for wanting to be treated with love and respect. Anyone who cannot honor your boundaries and respect your needs is not meant to stay in your life. 

Remember that respect, communication, honesty and accountability are just the bare minimum. So if you’re getting less than that you’re severely disrespecting yourself. Relationships of high value do not lack these basic elements of respect. Do not tolerate anything less, because doing so sends a message to yourself that you’re not worthy of better.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 05, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'WITH THE RIGHT PERSON YOU WONT NEED TO TRY SO HARD TO FEEL HEARO AND SEEN ↑'.

node.text:
I hope you remind yourself of this every time you wonder if it’s you. It’s not you. The right person for you won’t have you feeling like you’re the issue. If you’re constantly feeling like you’re too much or over exerting yourself just to feel seen — gather your self respect and walk the f away. 

No meaningful connection will have you begging for things that are common decency. Connection is about being seen for exactly who you are not having to hide your true self in fear of losing their affection. No real relationship will require you to self abandon in order to maintain closeness. You should feel comfortable showing up as you are and accepted for exactly that person. If you don’t feel seen and heard they may just not be capable of meeting you where you are. Accept it. Let go. The people who want to see you for you exist you just have to be willing to let go in order to replace them for the people you’re still holding onto.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 03, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, tree and text that says 'YOU CAN BE GOOD FOR SOMEONE WHO DOESN'T WANT WHAT'S GOOD FOR THEM'.

node.text:
Being good for someone doesn’t make you right for them. Being right for someone doesn’t make them good for you. How they make you feel should determine how you feel about them. Their behavior is a direct reflection of who they are.

Ignoring the truth for temporary bliss is one of the easiest ways to self abandon and waste your o time. Time is the most valuable currency because you will never get that back. Self love is choosing to no longer waste your time on how good you are for someone and realizing how good they are to you is what matters most.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Female on July 01, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'STOP BEING FLATTERED BY SOMEONE YOU THE BARE MINIMUM WHO IS LITERALLY GIVING THEEMLWA'.

node.text:
The bare minimum is not effort. The bare minimum is what someone is able to get away with to keep you around. It’s not something to be flattered or impressed by. Don’t forget that respect, communication and consistency are JUST the minimum. If you’re getting less than that which you probably are you’re tolerating crumbs and being loyal to a situation that is not serving you. 

Empower yourself to have higher standards. Quit allowing low quality behavior and unwanted energy to overpower your desire for a more meaningful and valuable connection. If you feel like there’s something missing or somethings off or that your effort is not reciprocated it’s your intuition asking you to pay attention. Don’t ignore it.
